HEADWORD: Retroact
<hw>Re`tro*act"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>retro- + act</ets>.]</ety> <def>To act backward, or in return; to
act in opposition; to be retrospective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

